    <title>A Survey on The Eisenbud-Green-Harris Conjecture</title>
    <summary>  The Eisenbud-Green-Harris (EGH) conjecture offers a generalization of the
famous Macaulay's theorem about the Hilbert functions of homogeneous ideals in
a polynomial ring $K[x_1,\ldots, x_n]$. In this survey paper, we provide a good
compilation of results on the EGH conjecture that have been obtained so far. We
discuss these results in terms of their approaches.
</summary>
